<span id="freeTextContainer17362717491454342187">Following the Sun brings together the all American dream boy and the troubled young lady trapped in a past of misunderstanding and hurt. It is a great example of one following his heart when others are against him and never giving up on LOVE. This book was a very powerful read for me, as it brought out memories from my own past of loving someone with an addiction amd helping them overcome it. It brought me to tears, it made me laugh, it made me shake my fist in anger and sometimes it even made m</span>
  <span id="freeText17362717491454342187" style="display:none">Following the Sun brings together the all American dream boy and the troubled young lady trapped in a past of misunderstanding and hurt. It is a great example of one following his heart when others are against him and never giving up on LOVE. This book was a very powerful read for me, as it brought out memories from my own past of loving someone with an addiction amd helping them overcome it. It brought me to tears, it made me laugh, it made me shake my fist in anger and sometimes it even made me do one or more together.<br /><br />Alisa delivers in true Mullen fashion once again. She has always written from the heart and is a straight shooter when it comes to the toughest of topics. She takes her passions in life to a whole new level and it clearly shows in her writing. Following the Sun is yet another perfect example of that. This book reminds its readers that everyone is fighting a battle even if we can't see it. It brings to light even the darkest sides of addiction and all that goes with it. Following the Sun doesn't sugar coat anything about the harsh realities of addiction. </span>
