<span id="freeTextContainer11857992858815298544">4 stars<br/><br/>Such an dark &amp; emotional read! This book deals with Sunny&apos;s (Ashley) addictions and thoughts of suicide that break your heart. She is such an emotional mess when she meets Nate. Have to admit I wasn&apos;t a fan of his at first but he just went &amp; made me fall in love with him! He is so determined to help Sunny &amp; in doing so changes himself. <br/><br/>Suicide &amp; addiction are a very tough topic &amp; I felt the book was written very well in explaining why Sunny felt the way she did &amp; how the addiction would t</span>
  <span id="freeText11857992858815298544" style="display:none">4 stars<br /><br />Such an dark &amp; emotional read! This book deals with Sunny's (Ashley) addictions and thoughts of suicide that break your heart. She is such an emotional mess when she meets Nate. Have to admit I wasn't a fan of his at first but he just went &amp; made me fall in love with him! He is so determined to help Sunny &amp; in doing so changes himself. <br /><br />Suicide &amp; addiction are a very tough topic &amp; I felt the book was written very well in explaining why Sunny felt the way she did &amp; how the addiction would take ahold of her. I also loved how she showed how it affected the people who care about you. Nate knew there was no cure for Sunny's addiction but he loved her more &amp; more everyday day. <br /><br />"After all, loving her had always been MY addiction and I refused to get help for that". <br /><br />Reviewed by: Penny<br /><br /></span>
