<div id="review_4123284380" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4123284380" />
    <a title="Bette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23824163-bette"><img alt="Bette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594682098p2/23824163.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4123284380?book_show_action=true">Jul 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bette" href="/user/show/23824163-bette">Bette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/24882614-following-the-sun">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4123284380" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12861326544447767179">Terrific Story &amp; Narration🎧 Engrossing &amp; Heartfelt!<br/><br/>Following the Sun: A Novel<br/>By: Alisa Mullen<br/>Narrated by: Jonathan Waters<br/><br/>I enjoyed this book immensely, the story is well written and original, it swept me in right from the start and captivated my attention the entire time. This book is not your typical romance novel, it is so much more, there is a lot of depth to the story and it touches on all of your emotions. It is my first book written by Alisa Mullen but it will not be my last, I am looking </span>
  <span id="freeText12861326544447767179" style="display:none">Terrific Story &amp; Narration🎧 Engrossing &amp; Heartfelt!<br /><br />Following the Sun: A Novel<br />By: Alisa Mullen<br />Narrated by: Jonathan Waters<br /><br />I enjoyed this book immensely, the story is well written and original, it swept me in right from the start and captivated my attention the entire time. This book is not your typical romance novel, it is so much more, there is a lot of depth to the story and it touches on all of your emotions. It is my first book written by Alisa Mullen but it will not be my last, I am looking forward to checking out more of her work. The characters are realistic, easy to relate to and connect with. Nate Wilson runs a bowling ally, a family business that was passed down to him. He has his routine down to the day, knows the ins and outs fo the business like the back of his hand. He and his friend also have a routine with the woman they are involved with but rules/routine goes out the window when someone catches his attention. Sunny, is one complicated and broken person with a lot of issues. Guilt is an ugly monster and it has ruled her life since she was a young girl. She has one goal in life and it is a dark one. Nathan sees her but does not understand her torment, but he is determined to save her. Her appearance at the bowling alley was a connection to her past, she finds another connection to her past as well. And that connection is probably what saves her and her misconceptions. This story contains a whole lot of heart, the story is beautifully plotted with plenty of drama, angst, a touch of humor here and there, heartfelt emotions and a romance that is meant to be. Alisa Mullen, thank you for the great story and emotional rollercoaster ride. <br /><br />🎧📚🎧 And for the fabulous narration, Jonathan Waters is a talented narrator and voice artist. He did a great job bringing the characters, humanizing them, giving each their own voice and personality. He had a complete understanding of each character he portrayed and took the roles and made it his own. You could hear how much heart he put in to his work as he captured the character’s emotions and projected them into his performance. He is an entertaining storyteller and a pleasure to listen to. Thank you for the great listen🎧</span>
  <a data-text-id="12861326544447767179" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


