  <span id="freeText3469446999438086630" style="display:none">Sweet N Sassy Book A Holics Rating: 5.0<br /><br />~~~~~~~~~~Dee's ★★★★★ Review~~~~~~~~~~<br /><br />Nate lives a contented life, no bills, no worries, a self owned business he loves and a trio of ladies that take care of his needs with no expectations. Then one day in walks a vision of loveliness that captures his heart....until she opens her mouth. He decides she is too toxic to muck up his busy, fulfilling life. So begins a journey for Nate and Sunny that takes them from sunny days to the darkest nightmares.<br /><br />One of those dark times had my heart aching for Nate when he had been invited to a lawyers office to sign some papers. The scene was so heartbreaking, I couldn't see the words on the page for the flowing tears. Then POW!! an explosive surprise is revealed that took my breath away! Whew! This is a deep, intense story that portrays the devastation of addiction and how it affects all those involved. But only unconditional love, forgiveness, compassion and the desire to live can overcome the disease....one day at a time. I was given this book in exchange for an honest review. Five Stars!<br /><br />~~~~~~~~~~Patricia's ★★★★★ Review~~~~~~~~~~<br /><br />This book was really an emotional ride. Sunny aka Ashley and Nate. Nate thinking that he would be a playboy forever different girls for sex. Really with no care in the world other that life is a Party. Then he meets someone who throws his life for a loop not realizing the emotional problems and addictions she has for awhile. Then all the melt down they both go through. Her learning the truth about something from her childhood and him learning that life is not just one big party. Do they finally realize that having an addiction is a life long process and something to fight for or do they let it all slip away?</span>
