<span id="freeTextContainer12157410655282309929">Following the Sun<br/>by Alisa Mullen<br/>An Emotional Romantic Roller coaster that Keeps You Guessing until the Very End!<br/><br/><br/>I was offered an ARC of this book in exchange for an honest review. I honestly loved this book. It was original, romantic, emotional and suspenseful. A true romance read, not an erotic book, it focuses on the character development and relationship which hook the reader and keeps them until the very end.<br/><br/>Ashley “Sunny” Sonterra is anything but sunny. She has struggled with her demons sin</span>
  <span id="freeText12157410655282309929" style="display:none">Following the Sun<br />by Alisa Mullen<br />An Emotional Romantic Roller coaster that Keeps You Guessing until the Very End!<br /><br /><br />I was offered an ARC of this book in exchange for an honest review. I honestly loved this book. It was original, romantic, emotional and suspenseful. A true romance read, not an erotic book, it focuses on the character development and relationship which hook the reader and keeps them until the very end.<br /><br />Ashley “Sunny” Sonterra is anything but sunny. She has struggled with her demons since her childhood, and as an adult, they continue to plague her. She self medicates her problems, which has created greater problems for her. Underneath it all, she is harboring a dark secret. One that she has never shared, and is planning that she is never going to.<br /><br />Nathan Wilson has never done serious relationships. He has women that he hooks up with, but never has developed true feelings for any of them. The first woman to ever steal is heart is Sunny, but will her darkness and secrets sabotage their relationship before it ever has a chance.<br /><br />I really enjoyed this read. The pacing was great. The unanswered questions throughout the book draw you in and keep you focused until the end. This is a must read!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12157410655282309929" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
