<div id="review_1198387089" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1198387089" />
    <a title="She Hearts Books" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27132461-she-hearts-books"><img alt="She Hearts Books" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1451179664p2/27132461.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1198387089?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="She Hearts Books" class="user" itemprop="url" name="She Hearts Books" href="/user/show/27132461-she-hearts-books">She Hearts Books</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1198387089" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4400052693909399155">Following the Sun is such an emotional read. The author writes of several issues like suicide and addictions which brings the dark side into the light in a really good way. She frames it within a love story that is quite the roller coaster. I couldn&apos;t put it down.<br/><br/> Sunny is battling the shadows of her past and a secret she has never shared. She struggles with thoughts of suicide and self medicates to the point of addiction trying to forget. She frequents Nate&apos;s bowling alley and he becomes intrig</span>
  <span id="freeText4400052693909399155" style="display:none">Following the Sun is such an emotional read. The author writes of several issues like suicide and addictions which brings the dark side into the light in a really good way. She frames it within a love story that is quite the roller coaster. I couldn't put it down.<br /><br /> Sunny is battling the shadows of her past and a secret she has never shared. She struggles with thoughts of suicide and self medicates to the point of addiction trying to forget. She frequents Nate's bowling alley and he becomes intrigued by her and wants to know more of her. He has no idea what her was getting into with her.<br /><br /> I give Following the Sun 4 hearts!</span>
